Important thing 1

Some important stuff we wanted you to know. Supports markdown

Queries

retrieveLabels

Returns [LabelResultItem]

Name Description
orderNumber - String!

Example

Query
query retrieveLabels($orderNumber: String!) {
  retrieveLabels(orderNumber: $orderNumber) {
    trackingId
    labelUrl
    packageId
  }
}
Variables
{"orderNumber": "xyz789"}
Response 
{
  "data": {
    "retrieveLabels": [
      {"trackingId": "abc123", "labelUrl": "abc123", "packageId": "abc123"}
    ]
  }
}

viewOrder

Fetch Order Details
Returns [Order]

Name Description
orderNumber - String!

Example

Query
query viewOrder($orderNumber: String!) {
  viewOrder(orderNumber: $orderNumber) {
    id
    orderNumber
    orderNumberText
    apiKey
    createdAt
    updatedAt
    isActive
    orderDetail {
      ...OrderDetailFragment
    }
    shipments {
      ...ShipmentFragment
    }
    recipient {
      ...AddressFragment
    }
    label {
      ...LabelFragment
    }
  }
}
Variables
{"orderNumber": "xyz789"}
Response 
{
  "data": {
    "viewOrder": [
      {
        "id": ID,
        "orderNumber": "xyz789",
        "orderNumberText": "xyz789",
        "apiKey": "abc123",
        "createdAt": DateTime,
        "updatedAt": DateTime,
        "isActive": false,
        "orderDetail": OrderDetail,
        "shipments": [Shipment],
        "recipient": Address,
        "label": Label
      }
    ]
  }
}

Types

ID

The ID scalar type represents a unique identifier, often used to refetch an object or as key for a cache. The ID type appears in a JSON response as a String; however, it is not intended to be human-readable. When expected as an input type, any string (such as "4") or integer (such as 4) input value will be accepted as an ID.

Example
object
Types

Int

The Int scalar type represents non-fractional signed whole numeric values. Int can represent values between -(2^31) and 2^31 - 1.

Example
123

The String scalar type represents textual data, represented as UTF-8 character sequences. The String type is most often used by GraphQL to represent free-form human-readable text.
